-- Piraeus Bank May Acquire Stakes in Two Greek Government-Controlled Lenders
-- Christos Ziotis
-- 2010-07-15T07:50:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/piraeus-bank-may-acquire-stakes-in-two-greek-government-controlled-lenders.html

          
          
             Piraeus Bank SA has submitted a
proposal to the Greek goverment to buy “significant stakes” in
two Greek state-controlled banks, Agricultural Bank of Greece SA
and Hellenic Postbank SA, the Athens bourse said in a filing
today.  
 All three banks were suspended from trading today, the
filing said. Piraeus Bank will hold a news conference at 11:30
a.m. in Athens, a bank spokesman said.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                                                 
                     
